:171,"target":171},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995","Note e giunte alle iscrizioni cristiane antiche della Sicilia","\u003Cspan>Antonio Ferrua, \u003Ci>Note e giunte alle iscrizioni cristiane antiche della Sicilia\u003C/i> (Vatican, 1989)\u003C/span>",{"type":175,"bibl":176},"discussion",[58],{"n":100,"url":101,"height":102,"width":103,"desc":104,"surfaceType":105},[],[156],[135,144,153,163,172],[157,166],[183,184,4,27,32,36,185,186,187,188,186,189,190,121],"isic001329","epitaph","catina","catania","italy","sicily","museo civico di catania","ancient greek",{"title":192,"body":193,"divs":194,"images":215},"ISic001329. Epitaph","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Τίμη [καὶ] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Ποιμ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ἑα\u003C/span>υτ[οῖς καὶ] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">το\u003C/span>[ῖς ἰδίοις] \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>[ἐποίησαν?] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΤΙΜΗ[...]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΠΟΙΜ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ΕΑ\u003C/span>ΥΤ[......]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ΤΟ\u003C/span>[........]\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>[........]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001329_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001329_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001329.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001329-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Kaibel: Τίμη; Ferrua: Τιμη[σίθεος; Korhonen: Τιμή\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"lines 1-2\">lines.1-2: \u003Cspan>Kirchhoff read ΠΟΙΩ which Ferrua (1941) corrected in ΠΟΙΗ (ἐ|ποίη[σε) but a Μ is clearly legible. Later, Ferrua (1989) suggested the supplement Ποιμ[ένιος]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Ferrua: ἑαυτ[ῷ]; Kaibel, Korhonen ἑαυτ[οῖς]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"lines 4-5\">lines.4-5: \u003Cspan>Kaibel: τὸ[ν τόπον] (scil. ἠγόρασαν)]; Ferrua: το[ῖς ἰδίο]|[ις πᾶσιν]; Korhonen: το[ῖς ἰδίοις]|[ἐποίησαν?]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Time and Poim--- made (this) for themselves and their relatives.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Time e Poim--- realizzarono (questo) per loro stessi e per i loro familiari.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The structure of the epitaph is influenced by Latin epigraphy (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">fecit sibi et suis\u003C/span>) and recurs often (but not exclusively) in Christian epitaphs: for this reason, Ferrua believed that the epitaph was Christian. The formula is used to indicate the dedicant, who is not yet dead, but the verb \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζάω\u003C/span> is often omitted (see Korhonen 2004: 88-89). According to Kaibel, followed by LGPN 3A: 429, \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Τίμη\u003C/span>, attested in the imperial age also in SEG 31.1327A, is the name of the first deceased, whereas \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Τιμησίθεος\u003C/span> suggested by Ferrua is not attested in that age. The second deceased could have been a \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ποιμήν\u003C/span> or a \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ποιμένιος\u003C/span> (as Ferrua suggested): the latter is attested in Christian age by literary sources. On the names, see Solin 1982: 1030 and 1256.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli>  \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">14.0508\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 199 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://bi